Moved some results from ring to semiring.    


--- 

In Mathlib.RingTheory.Ideal.Operations I moved two results from ring to semiring with the same proof, and  two I changed the proof.

Some comments on spaces. Otherwise LGTM.
This might be out of scope, but I think this equation should be reversed and renamed to `Ideal.comap_symm`. Also we need an `Ideal.map_symm`.

May be adding something like 

``` 
theorem comap_symm (I : Ideal R) (f : R ≃+* S) : I.comap f.symm= I.map (f) :=  
by rw[←@map_comap_of_equiv]; rfl

theorem map_symm (I : Ideal S) (f : R ≃+* S) : I.comap f= I.map f.symm :=  
by rw [← @comap_symm,@RingEquiv.symm_symm]
```
The latter should be flipped as well. Maybe make it into a simp lemma as well.

```suggestion
theorem map_isPrime_of_equiv {F' : Type*} [RingEquivClass F' R S] (f : F') {I : Ideal R}
    [IsPrime I] : IsPrime (map f I) := by
  have h: (I.map f) = (I.map ((f : R ≃+* S) : R →+* S)):= by congr
  rw [h, @map_comap_of_equiv _ _ _ _ I (f : R ≃+* S)]
  exact Ideal.IsPrime.comap (RingEquiv.symm (f : R ≃+* S))
```
